{"key":"processedPost-16328347","value":{"id":16328347,"first":16327739,"last":16328429,"when":1338777150,"utime":"06/04/12 05:32 AM","content":"The brown gypsum is generally regular powder gypsum with a binding agent so it can be applied on farms with mechanical equipment.&nbsp; The pellet gypsum will go through machinery where the powder gypsum would clog it up.&nbsp; It's fine to use if you're not certified organic.&nbsp; We can't use it on our mushroom substrates because the binding agent is a prohibited substance under USDA regs.<br /><br />If you use it, simply mix it in with your bulk substrate before adding water.&nbsp; Don't tear up your coffee grinder trying to grind it up.<br />RR","title":"Re: New Gypsum","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}